Chinesia Privacy Policy
Chinesia values your privacy and is committed to protecting it. This privacy policy explains our practices regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of information. This policy applies to all Chinesia products and services. If there are no separate privacy policies for specific products or services provided by us or our affiliates, and if there is an association between these products or services, this policy will also apply to other products or services provided by us or our affiliates, unless otherwise stated. This policy does not apply to products and services provided by third parties.
This policy covers the following aspects:
Important information and introduction about us
Personal data we collect
How and why we collect and use your personal data
Reasons for accessing your personal data
Your rights and choices regarding personal data
Reasons for using cookies
Steps we take to protect the security and confidentiality of your information
Retention period for your information
Your legal rights
1. Important information and introduction about us
Chinesia provides services ("Services") to you in accordance with the User Agreement and the following Privacy Policy. We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. By clicking "Agree" to this policy or by otherwise indicating your acceptance of this policy, or by actually downloading, installing, registering, or continuing to use Chinesia and/or Chinesia services after any changes to the relevant terms and policies, you are deemed to accept the new Privacy Policy.
2. Information collected and received in different states of the APP
Chinesia supports login methods with mobile numbers and third-party accounts. If you choose to log in with your mobile number, you will need to provide us with your phone number. We collect this information to identify and verify your identity. When you choose to log in to Chinesia products using third-party accounts such as Google, Facebook, Twitter, Kakao, Line, Naver, Apple ID, WeChat, QQ, etc., you agree that we may obtain the information you have authorized to share from these third-party platforms (including your phone number, nickname, profile picture, friend list, etc.). You also agree to link your third-party account with your Chinesia account, allowing you to log in and use Chinesia products directly with your third-party account and synchronize data across different devices. We will use the authorized personal information in accordance with the agreements with the third-party platforms and within the scope permitted by relevant laws and regulations. If you refuse to authorize Chinesia to obtain your shared information from third-party platforms, you will not be able to register and log in using methods such as Google, Facebook, Line, Naver, Apple ID, WeChat, QQ, nor will you be able to synchronize data using these third-party accounts.
After completing the registration of your Chinesia account, Chinesia will collect your personal information, such as your username, phone number, preferred language, and any voluntary personal information you provide in the system, including photos for your profile.
Chinesia will automatically collect and generate various usage information from other domains, including: service metadata, log data, IP addresses, third-party data and cookie information, as well as device information (device name, device model, hardware serial number, operating system and application version and type, language settings, resolution, random access memory of mobile devices, network access method, network quality data, mobile network information).
We also collect, use, and share various aggregated data, such as statistical data or audience characteristic data for any purpose. Aggregated data may be derived from your personal data, but under the law, such data should not be considered as personal data as they do not directly or indirectly disclose your identity. For example, we may aggregate your usage data to calculate the percentage of users accessing specific website features. However, if we combine or associate aggregated data with your personal data in a way that allows it to directly or indirectly identify your identity, we will treat the corresponding combined data as personal data and use it in accordance with this Privacy Policy. We do not collect any special categories of personal data related to you (including detailed information about your race or ethnicity, religion or philosophical beliefs, sexual orientation, political views, union membership, information related to your health status, and genetic and biometric data). We also do not collect any information related to criminal convictions and offenses.
When using our services, you can set up a personal profile, participate in language courses and vocabulary learning. There is no legal or contractual obligation for you to provide this data, but if you do not provide the data, we will not be able to provide the corresponding services.
To enhance the user experience of Chinesia products, Chinesia may collect the following personal information by accessing device permissions. If you do not agree to provide this personal information, you may not be able to use the additional features related to enhancing the user experience.
If you wish to upload your avatar and/or other image information to Chinesia, you can choose to authorize Chinesia to access your device's camera or photo album permissions.
If you agree to upload your voice recordings to Chinesia, you can choose to authorize Chinesia to access your device's microphone permissions.
If you agree to download course data (questions, audio, video content) to your device for offline course experience, you can choose to authorize Chinesia to access your device's storage permissions.
This additional feature collects relevant personal information from third-party service providers such as advertising push services.
Chinesia may cooperate with third-party service providers to integrate third-party services into Chinesia's products and/or services (such as advertising, links, or other forms of promotional content). Except for the explicitly mentioned third parties, Chinesia will not share your personal information provided to Chinesia or collected by Chinesia, such as phone numbers, nicknames, avatars, friend lists, with third-party service providers, nor will it represent third-party service providers in collecting your personal information. Third-party service providers accessed through Chinesia's products and/or services may have their own privacy policies, which are not bound by this Privacy Policy. Third-party service providers may collect personal information necessary to provide you with services in accordance with their own privacy policies. Chinesia will make reasonable efforts to require third-party service providers to comply with relevant laws and regulations when handling your personal information, and to request them to take appropriate confidentiality and security measures. However, Chinesia cannot guarantee that they will definitely take corresponding measures according to our requirements.
We share personal information with affiliated and non-affiliated service providers to help us conduct business, such as integrating and supporting certain services through application programming interfaces (APIs). These service providers may need access to read your necessary personal information to perform these tasks and are obligated to protect your personal information.
Some components of our services may be associated with third-party services that we do not own or control, such as third-party software development kits (SDKs) or third-party APIs integrated into our services to provide specific services or functionalities. Some of these third-party services may also require your personal information, such as your location or device information, to provide their services to you. When using such third-party services, you must comply with their terms of service and their privacy policies will also apply.
We periodically conduct technical testing and behavior audits on the SDKs or APIs provided by these partners or service providers and require them to comply with applicable laws, regulations, and agreements to ensure lawful and compliant collection and use of data.
The specific situations in which our services access third-party SDKs/APIs are as follows. Please note that the data processing types may change due to version upgrades, policy adjustments, and other reasons related to these third-party SDKs/APIs. You can refer to their official websites for more details:
（1）SDK for push notification, such as JPushSDK, FCM Google Push Service, Huawei Push.
The push notification service provides the ability to send messages and notifications to the app. After integrating JPushSDK, the push SDK will collect the personal information necessary for the implementation of the service and send messages and notifications to users through an encrypted channel. The personal information collected by the push SDK includes: ① Device information: used to identify unique users and ensure the accuracy of message delivery; optimize the push channel resources, we will integrate the push channel resources based on the activity of different apps on the device to improve the message delivery rate; ② Network and location information: optimize the network connection requests between the SDK and the push server to ensure the stability and continuity of the service; implement regional push functionality. In order for you to receive the information push function, we use the integrated push SDK to push users with discount activities, learning reminders, and information that serves our application business. The push-related SDK may read your device information (including connected wireless network device MAC, wireless network list, IMEI, device MAC address, network type, phone model, phone serial number, wireless network name) and location information. The Android permissions called to collect personal information may include: READ_PHONE_STATE; WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE; ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE; ACCESS_WIFI_STATE; ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION; ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION; GET_TASKS; READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE; WRITE_CALENDAR; READ_CALENDAR; RECORD_AUDIO; CAMERA. The above collected information and permissions are used to implement message push. Please note that for push SDKs, they will only be initialized and effective when you are using the corresponding brand of mobile device.
（2）SDKs for mobile crash logs and statistical page access and click events, such as Firebase and AppsFlyer.
Firebase is mainly used to track user usage within our application, helping us improve and provide better services. We will collect commonly used device information (such as IMEI/IMSI, SIM card serial number/MAC address, android_id, device model, operating system version), and network information. This information helps us develop more localized learning content for different users and helps us identify and resolve crash issues.
AppsFlyer is mainly used for app attribution analysis, helping apps make better marketing decisions. It collects commonly used device information, such as IMEI/IMSI, SIM card serial number/MAC address, android_id, device model, operating system version, and network information.
（3）SDKs for third-party payments, such as WeChat Pay, Alipay, PayPal, Apple In-App Purchase, and Google In-App Purchase.
We will collect commonly used device information (such as IMEI/IMSI, SIM card serial number/MAC address, android_id), network information, and GPS information for account login and secure risk control during the payment process.
（4）SDK for device identification, such as Alibaba Device Identification SDK. It collects device information including IMEI/IMSI, SIM card serial number/MAC address, Android ID, and network information for account login and secure risk control during the payment process.
（5）SDK for uploading images, such as avatars and screenshots of user feedback, Alibaba Cloud SDK.
（6）SDK for real-time online Chinese spoken language evaluation, such as Tencent Cloud Zhiling Spoken Language Evaluation.
3. Use of Information
Chinesia will use your personal data for the following general purposes to facilitate our legitimate interests:
(1) Providing, updating, maintaining, and protecting our services, website, applications, and business.
(2) Compliance with relevant laws, judicial procedures, or regulatory requirements.
(3) Statistical purposes.
(4) Sending marketing and transactional information about the service, including but not limited to emails, push notifications, text messages, and in-app messages.
(5) Settlement, account management, and other administrative matters.
(6) Investigation and assistance in preventing security issues and abusive behavior.
(7) Other purposes introduced to you at the time of collection.
Chinesia uses such information to fulfill your product and service requests and improve the services we provide to you. If you choose to share Chinesia's invitation link with friends, they will see your profile picture (if you have created one) and name on the landing page within Chinesia after clicking the link. You can delete and change this data at any time in your profile settings. All other information will not be displayed.
Please note: When you enter payment information for purchasing paid services, Chinesia does not receive or store the payment information mentioned above. Our payment service provider receives, stores, and uses this information to complete the transaction.
4. Retention
Chinesia will retain your personal data for as long as necessary to fulfill legitimate business interests, conduct audits, comply with (and demonstrate compliance with) legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. In determining the appropriate retention period for personal data, we consider the amount, nature, and sensitivity of the personal data, the risk of harm from unauthorized use or disclosure of the personal data, the purposes for which we process the personal data, whether we can achieve those purposes through other means, and the applicable legal requirements. You have the right to request deletion of your personal data by sending an email to octopustimes-study@zh-games.com. Please note that in such cases, we will retain relevant financial information in accordance with local laws.
5. COOKIES
Cookies are small pieces of data, typically containing an anonymous identifier, that are sent from a website to your computer's browser and stored on your computer's hard drive. You can set your browser to accept, reject, or notify you about cookies. If you choose to delete cookies that are already on your computer, you can find the cookies file or location through your browser's instructions. If you choose to reject all cookies, you may not be able to use certain features of the website.
6. Disclosure of Personal Information
We display your profile information (excluding your phone number and password) to people who browse the website in search of friends. Chinesia may rent, sell, or share your personal information with third parties unless it is with your permission, to provide products and services as requested by you, or in the following cases:
When Chinesia responds to subpoenas, court orders, legal processes, or to establish, exercise our legal rights or defend against legal claims.
When Chinesia believes it is necessary to provide information that assists in investigating, preventing, or taking action regarding illegal activities, fraud, potential threats to the safety of others, violations of the website's terms of service, or other legal requirements.
When you are using paid services as a student or employee, we may share your personal information with the respective educational institution or employer (as applicable) to monitor your use of the paid services.
If Chinesia is acquired or merged, your relevant information will be transferred. In such cases, Chinesia will notify you in advance, and the use of information will be subject to the new privacy policy.
We may share your data with other data processors such as Facebook, Google, etc. for targeted advertising purposes.
We require all third-party providers to respect the security of personal data and to handle personal data in accordance with the law. We do not allow third-party providers to use your personal data for their own purposes, and they are only allowed to process your personal data for specified purposes as instructed by us.
Please remember that any personal information you voluntarily disclose online may be collected and used by others. If you publicly post personal information on the publicly accessible internet, you may receive unsolicited responses.
7. Confidentiality and Security
We will take measures to use reasonable security safeguards tools that comply with industry standards to protect personal data from loss, theft, unauthorized access, disclosure, copying, improper use, or modification.
Your personal data is password protected and, unless otherwise stated in the privacy policy, only you and we can see it. You agree to keep your password confidential and not disclose it to others or allow others to obtain it.
Chinesia restricts employee access to your personal information, and our employees will only access this information when there is a legitimate reason, such as providing you with products or services or performing their tasks.
Chinesia has practical, electronic, and procedural safeguards that comply with regulations to protect your personal information. However, transmitting information over the internet is not 100% secure. Therefore, Chinesia cannot guarantee the security of the information you transmit to the website. In particular, you assume the risk when logging in and using the website's services. You need to limit others' use of your computer and ensure that it is protected against malicious code, spyware, viruses, trojans, and other software tools that can track the information you enter (including email addresses and payment-related information).
However, when you order a paid service, Chinesia will use secure payment service providers to ensure your secure payment.
Chinesia complies with the "Google Privacy Policy" and "Terms of Service".
8. Third-Party Websites
Websites linked to this website are not covered by this privacy policy. It is recommended that you carefully read the privacy statements of those websites to understand their procedures for collecting, using, and disclosing personal information.
9. Your Legal Rights
You have the right to:
Request access to your personal data (commonly known as a "data subject access request"). With this request, you can obtain a copy of the personal data we hold about you and check if we are processing it lawfully.
Request correction of the personal data that we hold about you. With this request, you can correct any incomplete or inaccurate data we hold about you, although we may need to verify the accuracy of the new data you provide to us.
Request erasure of your personal data. With this request, you can ask us to delete or remove your personal data when there is no legitimate reason for us to continue processing it. You also have the right to request the deletion or removal of your personal data in the following cases: you have successfully exercised your right to object to our processing of personal data (see below); we have unlawfully processed your information; or we must erase your personal data to comply with local laws. However, please note that when you submit a request, we may be unable to comply with your erasure request due to specific legal reasons (we will notify you of the specific reasons).
Object to processing of your personal data where we are relying on a legitimate interest (or those of a third party) and there is something about your particular situation which makes you want to object to processing on this ground as you feel it impacts on your fundamental rights and freedoms. You also have the right to object when we are processing your personal data for direct marketing purposes. In some cases, we may demonstrate that we have compelling legitimate grounds to process your information which override your rights and freedoms.
Request restriction of processing of your personal data. With this request, you can ask us to suspend the processing of your personal data in the following cases:
(a) You want us to establish the accuracy of the data;
(b) Our use of the data is unlawful, but you do not want us to erase the relevant data;
(c) You need us to retain the data, even if we no longer need it, because you need to establish, exercise, or defend legal claims; or you have objected to our use of your data, but we need to verify whether we have legitimate grounds to override your objection and use the relevant data.
Request the transfer of your personal data to you or a third party. We will provide your personal data to you or the third party you have chosen in a structured, commonly used, machine-readable format. Please note that this right only applies to personal data that you originally provided and consented to our use of, or to automated information that we use for the purposes of fulfilling our agreement with you.
Withdraw consent at any time (where we rely on consent to process your personal data). However, this will not affect the lawfulness of any processing carried out before you withdraw your consent. If you withdraw your consent, we may not be able to provide certain products or services to you. If this is the case at the time you withdraw your consent, we will provide you with relevant notice. If you wish to exercise any of the above rights, please contact us as described below.
Access to your personal data (or exercise any other rights) free of charge. However, if your request is clearly unfounded, repetitive, or excessive, we may charge a reasonable fee or refuse to comply with your request. We may need to request specific information from you to help us confirm your identity and ensure your right to access your personal data (or exercise any other rights). This is a security measure to ensure that personal data is not disclosed to any person who has no right to receive it. We may also contact you to ask for further information in relation to your request in order to expedite our response. We will try to respond to all legitimate requests within 1 month. Occasionally, it may take longer than 1 month if your request is particularly complex or you have made multiple requests. In this case, we will notify you and keep you updated in a timely manner.
Protection of Minors
We attach great importance to the protection of personal information of minors. In principle, we do not provide products/services to minors. We only provide platform products/services to adults and assume that you have the corresponding legal capacity when using our platform products/services. If you are a minor, before using our platform products/services, we require you to have your parents or guardians carefully read this policy and use our products or services or provide information to us with the consent of your parents or guardians. You and your parents or guardians shall bear all consequences in accordance with the law. In the case of collecting personal information of minors with the consent of parents or guardians for using our products or services, we will only use, share, transfer, or disclose this information when permitted by laws and regulations, explicitly consented by parents or guardians, or necessary for the protection of minors. If you are the parent or guardian of a minor, please pay attention to whether the minor under your guardianship is using our products or services with your authorized consent. If you have any questions about the personal information of the minor you are supervising, please contact us through the contact information provided in this policy.
Contacting Chinesia and Feedback
When you contact us or submit an application for dispute resolution, in order to ensure the security of your account and system, we may need you to provide necessary personal information and business entity information to verify your user identity.
In order to facilitate communication with you, help you solve problems as soon as possible, or record the handling plan and results of relevant issues, we may retain your communication/call records and related content with us (including account information such as mobile phone number, other information you provide to prove relevant facts, or contact information you leave). If you consult, complain, or provide suggestions regarding specific services, we will use the information within your account with your consent.
In order to provide services and improve service quality, we may also use your other information, including relevant information you provide when contacting customer service, and questionnaire reply information you send to us when participating in surveys.
